    <dashboard enable-sort-zone-taborder='true' name='Gender vs. Purchasing Behavior'>
      <style />
      <size maxheight='651' maxwidth='1350' minheight='651' minwidth='1350' preset-index='17' sizing-mode='fixed' />
      <zones>
        <zone forceUpdate='true' h='37942' id='4' type-v2='text' w='60963' x='296' y='8909'>
          <formatted-text>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='14'>Findings:</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>Æ </run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'>While male users show higher overall engagement with more orders and higher expenditure, female users tend to have a slightly higher average order value.</run>
            <run>Æ&#10;&#10;</run>
            <run bold='true' fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='14'>Recommendations:</run>
            <run fontcolor='#000000' fontname='Times New Roman' fontsize='12'> To boost engagement among female users, Zomato should utilize targeted feedback tools and personalized marketing focused on value-driven, exclusive restaurant partnerships. By applying customized advertising and incentivizing feedback, the platform can improve user satisfaction and strengthen its customer base among this demographic.</run>
          </formatted-text>
        </zone>
